abstract: This time the automaker is in talks to combine with Peugeot, just months after its attempts to join with Renault failed.

abstract: Digressions. Mix-ups. Mistakes. Joseph R. Biden Jr. has a choppy speaking style that could undermine his message at a time when he needs to attract more voters and donors.
snippet: Digressions. Mix-ups. Mistakes. Joseph R. Biden Jr. has a choppy speaking style that could undermine his message at a time when he needs to attract more voters and donors.
lead_paragraph: WEST POINT, Iowa — Joseph R. Biden Jr. was making an impassioned case for protecting undocumented immigrants one recent Sunday when he abruptly stopped himself.

abstract: Despite the lack of consensus, a new survey finds that almost two-thirds of the public favors Democratic approaches.
snippet: Despite the lack of consensus, a new survey finds that almost two-thirds of the public favors Democratic approaches.
lead_paragraph: When Americans are asked whether they support a “Medicare for all” system that would replace all current insurance with a generous government program, a majority often say yes. But when they’re asked follow-up questions, they often reveal that they’re not familiar with the details of that plan — or that they would also be happy with other Democratic policy proposals.

abstract: America’s need for a savior outweighs any interest in what he or she does in bed.
snippet: America’s need for a savior outweighs any interest in what he or she does in bed.
lead_paragraph: Pete Buttigieg vaulted into the top four of a crowded Democratic presidential field because he has an agile intellect, is fiercely articulate and both espouses and embodies a fresh perspective that many voters of all stripes crave.

abstract: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
snippet: Trailing in the money race, tripped up by their own missteps and perceived by some as less electable, nonwhite candidates find themselves well back of the leaders.
lead_paragraph: When the Democratic primary contest began last winter, it featured the most racially diverse field in history, with two black senators, a Latino former cabinet secretary, an Asian-American businessman and the first American Samoan elected to Congress. But 10 months later, the Democratic field has a top tier of four white candidates, three of them men.

abstract: Selective deficit hysteria has done immense damage.
snippet: Selective deficit hysteria has done immense damage.
lead_paragraph: So the federal budget deficit just hit $1 trillion (actually $984 billion, but close enough). That’s about $300 billion more than the Congressional Budget Office was projecting in the summer of 2017, before the Trump tax cut was enacted. And basically everybody yawned.

abstract: When he goes low, Democrats are supposed to go high. Except, it turns out, going low feels wonderful.
snippet: When he goes low, Democrats are supposed to go high. Except, it turns out, going low feels wonderful.
lead_paragraph: Most weeks my Mondays unfold in a well-practiced routine: brush teeth, wash face, walk dog. This morning, I added a new step: spend 15 minutes scrolling through Twitter to see whether anyone had synced that delicious footage of President Trump’s face falling on Sunday — as the World Series crowd is booing him — with the R.E.M. song “Everybody Hurts.”
